{
  "texts": [
    "We utilize the train split of the Me-tRex dataset for instruction tuning and evaluate on the test dataset derived from the VerilogEval benchmark [3].Our fine-tuning experiments are mainly focused on the Mixtral-8x7b and Llama3-8b models.",
    "We employ LoRA [32], a parameter-efficient fine-tuning technique that decomposes the weight matrices into smaller, manageable low-rank matrices.",
    "This approach significantly reduces the computational load and memory demands associated with fine-tuning LLMs.",
    "We fine-tune a LoRA adapter per metric using an instruction dataset of Verilog code and metric reasoning pair.",
    "Additionally, we quantize the LLMs to 4 bits to reduce the memory footprint."
  ]
}